-- Amazon.com Ships Kindle Touch 3G Today, Was Planned for April 27
-- B y   L i s a   R a p a p o r t
-- 2012-04-20T20:09:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-20/amazon-com-ships-kindle-touch-3g-today-was-planned-for-april-27.html
Amazon.com Inc. (AMZN)  has started
shipping the Kindle Touch 3G to customers in 175 countries and
territories around the world, the Seattle-based company said
today in a statement.  The device, which Amazon previously said would ship April
27, is an electronic-reader with 3G wireless and a two-month
battery life, Amazon said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lisa Rapaport in New York at 
 lrapaport1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
